<subSubSection id="C30F65165D31AF4B66FC604078A8F91A" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BAA369D5D31AF4B66FC6040784EFA42" blockId="1.[151,1437,1124,1692]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B66FC60407A63FBF9" bold="true" box="[151,359,1124,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Taxonomic notes.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B6C5D31AF4B67046041792BFBF9" author="Holloway, J. D." box="[367,559,1125,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" pagination="1 - 268" refId="ref8779" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2008) The Moths of Borneo: Family Noctuidae, subfamilies Rivulinae, Phytometrinae, Herminiinae, Hypeninae and Hypenodinae. Malayan Nature Journal, 60 (1 - 4), 1 - 268." type="journal article" year="2008">Holloway (2008)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D1E5D31AF4B64B860417F59FBF9" authority="Wileman, 1915" authorityName="Wileman" authorityYear="1915" box="[723,1117,1124,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Nodaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B64B8604178AEFBF9" box="[723,938,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Nodaria terminalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B6C5D31AF4B65DA60417F59FBF9" author="Wileman, A. E." box="[945,1117,1124,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" pagination="34 - 40" refId="ref9178" refString="Wileman, A. E. (1915) New species of Heterocera from Formosa. Entomologist, 48, 34 - 40." type="journal article" year="1915">Wileman, 1915</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="54AE883F5D31AF4B620760417F9AFBF9" box="[1132,1182,1125,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">type</typeStatus>
locality: Taiwan) with 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D1E5D31AF4B66FC60AD793CFB25" authority="Hampson, 1898" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1898" box="[151,568,1161,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mixomelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B66FC60AD7A84FB25" box="[151,384,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Mixomelia decipiens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B6C5D31AF4B67ED60AD793CFB25" author="Hampson, G. F." box="[390,568,1161,1187]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" pagination="698 - 724" refId="ref8734" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1898) The moths of India. Supplementary paper to the volumes in &quot; The Fauna of British India &quot;. Part III. Journal of the Bombay Natural History Society, 11, 698 - 724." type="journal article" year="1898">Hampson, 1898</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="54AE883F5D31AF4B642D60AD797CFB25" box="[582,632,1161,1187]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">type</typeStatus>
locality: Khasi Hills, 
<collectingCountry id="F302760D5D31AF4B650560AD78ADFB22" box="[878,937,1161,1188]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">India</collectingCountry>
) and recorded the geographical range of this species as Himalaya, 
<collectingCountry id="F302760D5D31AF4B67E660897AE6FB41" box="[397,482,1197,1223]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, northern Ryukyus, Borneo, and also gave his view that “the synonymy above may need to be reviewed when variability in the basal ornamentation of the aedeagus vesica can be assessed over a wider range of material.” Though examining abundant material from different collecting localities, we have the opportunity to review the 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D1E5D31AF4B6711613E7953FAB5" authorityName="in Nilgiri Hills, Khasi Hills" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[378,599,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B6711613E7953FAB5" box="[378,599,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Herminia decipiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex. Our study shows that 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D1E5D31AF4B65A8613E7F53FAB5" authorityName="Wileman" authorityYear="1915" box="[963,1111,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Nodaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B65A8613E7F53FAB5" box="[963,1111,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">H. terminalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D1E5D31AF4B637B613E7E98FAB5" authorityName="in Nilgiri Hills, Khasi Hills" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[1296,1436,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B637B613E7E20FAB5" box="[1296,1316,1306,1331]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B6359613D7E98FAB5" box="[1330,1436,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">decipiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is restricted to 
<collectingCountry id="F302760D5D31AF4B670361197ABAFAD1" box="[360,446,1341,1367]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. The true 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D1E5D31AF4B6441611A79B2FAD1" authorityName="in Nilgiri Hills, Khasi Hills" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[554,694,1341,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B6441611A793AFAD1" box="[554,574,1342,1367]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B6427611979B2FAD1" box="[588,694,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">decipiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in Nilgiri Hills, Khasi Hills, South 
<collectingCountry id="F302760D5D31AF4B62BE61197E1FFAD1" box="[1237,1307,1341,1367]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">China</collectingCountry>
, Indochina, Malay Peninsula. The populations occurring in other regions represent three new species, i.e. 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D1E5D31AF4B62AA61467E3DFAFD" authority="Owada &amp; Wu, 2019" authorityName="Owada &amp; Wu" authorityYear="2019" box="[1217,1337,1377,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yuksam" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B62AA61467E3DFAFD" box="[1217,1337,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">H. yuksam</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25257F45D31AF4B632A61457E98FAFD" box="[1345,1436,1377,1403]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B632A61457E98FAFD" bold="true" box="[1345,1436,1377,1403]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(East 
<collectingCountry id="F302760D5D31AF4B66B261A17A1BFA19" box="[217,287,1413,1439]" name="Nepal" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, Sikkim), 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D1E5D31AF4B67F861A27901FA19" authority="Owada &amp; Wu, 2019" authorityName="Owada &amp; Wu" authorityYear="2019" box="[403,517,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borneo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B67F861A27901FA19" box="[403,517,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">H. borneo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25257F45D31AF4B646661A1796CFA19" box="[525,616,1413,1439]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B646661A1796CFA19" bold="true" box="[525,616,1413,1439]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(endemic to Borneo), 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D1E5D31AF4B650C61A27F23FA19" authority="Owada &amp; Wu, 2019" authorityName="Owada &amp; Wu" authorityYear="2019" box="[871,1063,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amamioshima" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B650C61A27F23FA19" box="[871,1063,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">H. amamioshima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25257F45D31AF4B624461A17F8EFA19" box="[1071,1162,1413,1439]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B624461A17F8EFA19" bold="true" box="[1071,1162,1413,1439]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(Amami-oshima Island, Shimo-Koshikijima 
<collectingCountry id="F302760D5D31AF4B6710618D7ABBFA45" box="[379,447,1449,1475]" name="Iceland" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Island</collectingCountry>
and Kagoshima in South Kyushu).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA369D5D31AF4B66AC61E87A28F9D5" blockId="1.[151,1437,1124,1692]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B66AC61E87A46FA61" bold="true" box="[199,322,1484,1511]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D1E5D31AF4B671061EA7953FA61" authorityName="in Nilgiri Hills, Khasi Hills" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[379,599,1485,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B671061EA7953FA61" box="[379,599,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Herminia decipiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex can be separated from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D1E5D31AF4B623761EA7FC3FA61" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[1116,1223,1486,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Herminia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B623761EA7FC3FA61" box="[1116,1223,1486,1511]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Herminia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the less distinct wing fasciae, the more and less dark shade at posterior half part of forewing, the markedly large hairy tibial sheath and minute tarsus of male foreleg (
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B6C5D31AF4B6408623179F2F9A9" author="Owada, M." box="[611,758,1557,1583]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580" refId="ref8901" refString="Owada, M. (1987) A taxonomic study on the subfamily Herminiinae of Japan (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae). National Science Museum, Tokyo, 208 pp." type="book" year="1987">Owada 1987</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 206), and the rather long valval costal process and apical part of valve.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA369D5D31AF4B66AC627878A8F91A" blockId="1.[151,1437,1124,1692]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis id="B961EA8F5D31AF4B66AC62787A65F9F1" bold="true" box="[199,353,1628,1655]" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Distribution.</emphasis>
The Himalayan region, South 
<collectingCountry id="F302760D5D31AF4B64D1627979F2F9F1" box="[698,758,1629,1655]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">India</collectingCountry>
, South 
<collectingCountry id="F302760D5D31AF4B652162797894F9F1" box="[842,912,1629,1655]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">China</collectingCountry>
, Indochina, Malay Peninsula, Borneo, 
<collectingCountry id="F302760D5D31AF4B632862797E9CF9F1" box="[1347,1432,1629,1655]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F302760D5D31AF4B66FC62A57BD3F91D" box="[151,215,1665,1691]" name="Japan" pageId="1" pageNumber="580">Japan</collectingCountry>
(Amami-oshima Is., Shimo-Koshikijima Is. and South Kyushu).
</paragraph>
